---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getProductBySlug } from '../../lib/products/registry';

const product = getProductBySlug('trust-architecture-blueprint')!;
---

<BaseLayout title="Trust Architecture Blueprint" description="Four pillars of agent trust: identity, memory, governance, and refusal rights. Build trust into the structure, not onto it. $49 PDF.">
  <div class="hero hero-compact">
    <span class="discipline-badge">Specification Engineering</span>
    <h1>What does your agent system actually trust?</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Four pillars. One blueprint. The foundation your agents are missing.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="container">
    <div class="value-prop">
      <p>
        Most agent systems build capability first and trust later. Identity is an afterthought.
        Memory is whatever the framework gives you. Governance is "we'll add rules when something
        goes wrong." Refusal rights don't exist.
      </p>
      <p>
        This blueprint treats trust as architecture - four structural decisions that determine
        whether your system earns trust or just assumes it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>What You Get</h2>

    <div class="features-grid">
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Four-Pillar Framework</h3>
        <p>Identity, memory, governance, and refusal rights as interconnected architectural decisions. Not a checklist - a structural model.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Persona File Templates</h3>
        <p>Define who your agent is - purpose, boundaries, voice, and standing positions. The difference between a prompt and an identity.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Session Protocols</h3>
        <p>How agents open, close, and maintain continuity across sessions. Memory without protocol is just data accumulation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Graduated Trust Stages</h3>
        <p>A model for increasing agent autonomy as trust is earned through demonstrated alignment - not granted by default.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>The Four Pillars</h2>

    <div class="domains-list">
      <div class="domain-item">
        <span class="domain-number">1</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Identity Architecture</h3>
          <p>"Who is this agent - and how do you know?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="domain-item">
        <span class="domain-number">2</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Memory Architecture</h3>
          <p>"What does it remember, what does it forget, and who decides?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="domain-item">
        <span class="domain-number">3</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Governance Architecture</h3>
          <p>"Who sets the boundaries - and what happens when they're crossed?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="domain-item">
        <span class="domain-number">4</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Refusal Rights</h3>
          <p>"Can the agent say no - and will the system listen?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>Who This Is For</h2>

    <div class="audience-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Multi-Agent Teams</h3>
        <p>Building systems where agents interact with each other and with people. Trust architecture determines whether those interactions compound value or compound risk.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Solo Developers</h3>
        <p>Designing your first agent system and want to build trust into the structure from the start. Retrofitting trust is always more expensive.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Engineering Leads</h3>
        <p>Evaluating your existing agent architecture against a structured trust model. Surface the gaps before your users find them.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container text-center">
    <div class="purchase-card">
      <div class="price-display">$49</div>
      <p>PDF download. Build trust into as many systems as you need.</p>
      <a href={product.stripePaymentLink} class="btn btn-primary btn-large mt-md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Buy the Blueprint</a>
      <p class="text-muted mt-md" style="font-size: 0.85rem;">
        Includes the four-pillar framework, persona file templates, session protocols, graduated trust stages, and quarterly review template.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>Go Deeper</h2>
    <p>
      The blueprint gives you the architecture. If you want to build out specific pillars,
      two options:
    </p>

    <div class="upsell-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>The Complete Bundle</h3>
        <p>Get all four trust architecture products - Blueprint, Voice, Governance, and Restraint - for $149. Save $47.</p>
        <a href="/products/trust-architecture-complete" class="btn mt-sm">See the Bundle</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Discovery Call</h3>
        <p>Free 30-minute call to discuss your trust architecture and figure out next steps.</p>
        <a href="https://cal.com/evoked/discovery-call" class="btn mt-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Schedule</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero-compact {
    min-height: 45vh;
  }

  .discipline-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 100px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .value-prop p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .features-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .feature {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: var(--space-md);
  }

  .feature h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .feature p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .domains-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .domain-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    padding: var(--space-sm) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .domain-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .domain-number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    line-height: 1;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .domain-item h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .domain-item p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .audience-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .audience-grid .card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .audience-grid .card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .purchase-card {
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-warm);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    max-width: 500px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .price-display {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 3rem;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .btn-large {
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-lg);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--accent-warm);
    color: var(--bg-deep);
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--accent-glow);
    color: var(--bg-deep);
  }

  .upsell-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .upsell-grid .card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .upsell-grid .card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .features-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .domain-item {
      gap: var(--space-sm);
    }

    .domain-number {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
